Create a navigation bar using HTML and CSS.
Use HTML to create a navigation bar with appropriate tags such as <ul> and <li>.
Use CSS to style the navigation bar with appropriate properties such as background-color, font-size, and padding.


HTML:--
<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">About Us</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
    <li><a href="#">Contact Us</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

CSS:--
nav {
  background-color: #333; /* set the background color */
  padding: 10px; /* add some padding */
}

ul {
  list-style-type: none; /* remove the bullet points from the list */
  margin: 0; /* remove the default margin */
  padding: 0; /* remove the default padding */
  overflow: hidden; /* create a new block formatting context and prevent floats from escaping */
}

li {
  float: left; /* float the list items to the left */
}

li a {
  display: block; /* make the links take up the entire width of the list item */
  color: white; /* set the font color */
  text-align: center; /* center the text */
  padding: 14px 16px; /* add some padding */
  text-decoration: none; /* remove the underline */
  font-size: 18px; /* set the font size */
}

li a:hover {
  background-color: #111; /* change the background color on hover */
}
